  "doc_id": "28984",
  "text": "The Bcl-2 family includes antiapoptotic and pro-apoptotic proteins, which are major regulators of the mitochondrial membrane potential. [CITATION_1] The antiapoptotic proteins are Bcl-2 and Bcl-xl, whereas Bax and Bid are distributed in the cytoplasm to promote apoptosis. There is a significant positive correlation between Bcl-2 family and NF-κB. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Many tumor-associated signaling pathways are associated with Bcl-2 family proteins, and data have shown that EVO plus GEM significantly reduced the expression of Bcl-2 and Bcl-xl, suggesting increased apoptosis. EVO may not only inhibit NF-κB but also may regulate the apoptotic pathways of cancer cells.",
